result.formatted_address: Tsan Tuen Rd, Cheung Chau, Hong Kong
result.name: Heima Heima

reviews.text:
Heima Heima is a water front coffee shop with fantastic view and a cozy Scandinavian design, simple yet beautiful. Their collection of books on coffee and coffee shop design is very nice too. Make sure you check out their bookshelf :)

The food served is definitely lit. The Taro & Honey Chiffon Cake on the right is quite special, as you don’t often get mashed taro as cream on cake. I love it dearly, especially the hint of honey. The chiffon cake was quite spongy. The Matcha and Red Beans Pudding was very decent too, with strong green tea flavour and not overly sweet at all. Everything is just so right to the point and very enjoyable.

Not sure about what tea it is, as my friend placed the order, but the tea was really nice to go with the dessert. A perfect fika for a Saturday afternoon.
Nice cozy little place with friendly service. Serves good coffee and dessert too
Nice place to grab some food while waiting for a ferry.

A cozy little place, with very differently calm atmosphere to the rest of Cheung Chau. Desserts are super delicious. Always come to sit and chill in the past two years. Very nice couple owners as well. Add oil!

Very small menu and you'd better stick to Today's Special coz lots of things on menu are not available. 

We ordered All Day Breakfast. Ingredients are of good quality. 

For someone who put so much effort to make the place looks nice, the owner is not the slightest friendly to contribute to a more friendly atmosphere.

They don't accept reservation which is somewhat unreasonable consider they are quite out of the way to get to and the cafe is small.
